description: "Repository pattern rules"
alwaysApply: true
---

# Repository Rules

- All DB access must go through repository
- Do NOT inject DbContext into Controller

# Design
- Use interface for each repository
- Keep repository focused on data access only

# Query
- Return IQueryable only when necessary
- Prefer returning DTO or projection

# Example

Good:
return await _context.Users
    .AsNoTracking()
    .Select(x => new UserDto { Id = x.Id, Name = x.Name })
    .ToListAsync();

Bad:
return await _context.Users.ToListAsync();